00:02:35,708 --> 00:02:37,583
Oriana is likely
to use for the dea--

14
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:38,625
[KAMIJO] Tsuchimikado...

15
00:02:38,708 --> 00:02:40,291
I just shook hands
with a woman...

16
00:02:40,375 --> 00:02:43,250
and when I did, I felt my
Imagine Breaker do something.

17
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,458
For now I can't tell
you who she is, exactly...

18
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:49,000
[KAMIJO] but I think it's safe
to say that she's not a student.

19
00:02:49,083 --> 00:02:49,916
[TSUCHIMIKADO] This woman...

20
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,750
is she carrying
a large package?

21
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:54,750
[KAMIJO] Yeah... She's got
what looks to be a signboard.

22
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:56,958
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Okay,
where are you right now?

23
00:02:57,625 --> 00:02:59,666
Right now? I'm following
her, of course...

24
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,416
I'm going to send
you my GPS coordinates

25
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:03,708
so you'll be able to
see where we are, kay?

26
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:11,333
She saw me!

27
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:24,250
[KAMIJO breathing heavy]

28
00:03:31,166 --> 00:03:32,666
Where is she? Which one?

29
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:34,750
Over there...
wearing a work uniform...

30
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:36,541
Woman with
the blonde hair.

31
00:03:43,041 --> 00:03:45,375
[ORIANA] Looks like we've
got two pros on the scene.

32
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:47,625
My instructions were
not to engage anybody,

33
00:03:47,708 --> 00:03:50,583
but something tells me
they won't make it easy.

34
00:03:50,916 --> 00:04:01,708
♪

35
00:04:01,791 --> 00:04:04,625
I'm not sure why,
but her behavior feels off.

36
00:04:04,708 --> 00:04:07,041
[TSUCHIMIKADO] I wonder
if she's changed her mind?

37
00:04:09,208 --> 00:04:10,750
[heavy breathing]

38
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,208
She's in the bus terminal?

39
00:04:12,291 --> 00:04:14,875
Nah, this's just a
servicing station.

40
00:04:19,708 --> 00:04:21,583
It's a trap...! Get down, Kami!

41
00:04:21,666 --> 00:04:23,041
[STIYL] Actually, you're up.

42
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:28,625
[KAMIJO] You screwing with me?

43
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:30,750
Nope... In fact, I think
that was an excellent

44
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:33,083
example of teamwork.
Having a clear division

45
00:04:33,166 --> 00:04:35,250
of labor makes things
go more smoothly.

46
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:37,291
Ehhh.

47
00:04:37,375 --> 00:04:38,666
If you're playing
games with me...!

48
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:39,625
Well I'm not,
kid. So go ahead

49
00:04:39,708 --> 00:04:41,291
and finish
your job, already!

50
00:04:44,291 --> 00:04:46,291
And what exactly
is my job here?!

51
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:54,500
♪

52
00:04:54,583 --> 00:04:55,833
Okay, Stiyl...

53
00:04:55,916 --> 00:04:57,791
You post the necessary
runes and stand by here...

54
00:04:57,875 --> 00:05:00,041
As for me... I'll
pin down the courier.

55
00:05:00,125 --> 00:05:01,583
Roger that.

56
00:05:02,583 --> 00:05:04,791
Well...? What are
you gonna do now, Kami?

57
00:05:04,875 --> 00:05:05,875
[TSUCHIMIKADO] I think
it's probably safer

58
00:05:05,958 --> 00:05:07,833
for you to stay here.

59
00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:08,958
I don't know...

60
00:05:09,041 --> 00:05:10,500
I agree with him...

61
