she's going to get away.

66
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:33,333
Yeah? Well what else do
you expect me to do? Ah!

67
00:05:35,375 --> 00:05:37,125
Euhhh...

68
00:05:40,208 --> 00:05:41,208
[KAMIJO] Got her!

69
00:05:41,291 --> 00:05:43,208
[rumbling]

70
00:05:46,083 --> 00:05:47,333
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Whenever
you're ready, Kami...

71
00:05:47,416 --> 00:05:49,833
Huh...? What am
I supposed to do?

72
00:05:51,916 --> 00:05:53,208
[grunts]

73
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,291
[power yell]

74
00:05:58,916 --> 00:06:08,875
♪

75
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:23,041
[grunts]

76
00:06:27,291 --> 00:06:30,458
A note from Oriana Thomson,
also known as "Route Disturb."

77
00:06:30,541 --> 00:06:32,541
Now she's toying with us!

78
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:34,541
[chuckles]

79
00:06:34,625 --> 00:06:36,041
Ah!

80
00:06:36,125 --> 00:06:37,833
[BOY STUDENT 9A]
Oh...! Excuse me!

81
00:06:37,916 --> 00:06:39,416
Are you alright, miss?

82
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,791
Ah...

83
00:06:40,875 --> 00:06:43,750
Oh, no... I should be
the one apologizing to you.

84
00:06:45,583 --> 00:06:47,833
[TSUCHIMIKADO] This spell is
called "Four Ways to Truth."

85
00:06:47,916 --> 00:06:51,291
Using this, we'll be able
to pinpoint Oriana's location.

86
00:06:51,375 --> 00:06:52,541
But, won't it hurt you?

87
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,208
I thought you weren't
supposed to use magic.

88
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:55,458
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
And that is why...

89
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:56,916
I'm gonna' go get some help.

90
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,375
Hm?

91
00:07:04,083 --> 00:07:05,416
[STIYL] Traveling on the wind...

92
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:09,000
conveying not air but will
to the specified location.

93
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:18,916
♪

94
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:31,375
Uh.

95
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,000
"Traveling on the wind...

96
00:07:35,083 --> 00:07:39,375
conveying not air but will to
the specified location." Right?

97
00:07:40,291 --> 00:07:44,666
[screaming]

98
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:45,958
Stiyl!

99
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:47,083
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Kami!

100
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:49,208
Go give Stiyl
a pat on the back.

101
00:07:49,291 --> 00:07:52,791
[STIYL screaming]

102
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:57,333
[STIYL heavy exhale]

103
00:07:57,416 --> 00:07:59,416
[breathing heavy]

104
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,625
That hurt...! What
did she just do to me...?

105
00:08:01,708 --> 00:08:04,291
Some kind of trace prevention
spell or something...?

106
00:08:04,375 --> 00:08:06,083
Just as general protection?

107
00:08:06,166 --> 00:08:07,250
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Nope...
I don't think it's

108
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,958
something that simple.

109
00:08:09,041 --> 00:08:10,375
What I think...

110
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:12,333
is that there's a specialized
interception spell...

111
00:08:12,416 --> 00:08:14,166
One that has been
specifically designed to react

112
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:16,750
automatically to
Stiyl's personal magic.

113
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,041
So what does that mean...?

114
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:19,958
Stiyl's been singled
out so he can no longer

115
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:22,375
direct any magic
towards Oriana?

116
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:24,208
[STIYL] This is serious...

117
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:26,916
That's a hell of a
thing to have prepared.

118
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
It's a pretty big deal
for one person to be able to

119
00:08:29,083 --> 00:08:32,125
detect a specific life
force, trace it back...

120
00:08:32,208 --> 00:08:34,583
and then apply
a counterattack...

121
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:37,666
But I guess that's
Route Disturb for you, huh?

122
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:39,875
Sorry? Route Disturb?

123
00:08:39,958 --> 00:08:43,416
The other name that
Oriana Thomson goes by.

124
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,500
[STIYL] This may sound crazy,
but there's something about

125
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:48,666
her particular method that
strikes me as familiar.

126
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:51,083
I must be wrong though,
don't you think...?

127
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:53,166
There's no way she could
be in possession of one.

128
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:55,166
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Well...
oddly enough... I was just

129
00:08:55,250 --> 00:08:57,750
thinking that there's no
other possible explanation.

130
00:08:57,833 --> 00:09:00,291
[STIYL] Are you serious...?
But if it's really true,

131
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:02,125
that would mean
Oriana's a sorceress,

132
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:03,875
not a magician
like we thought.

133
00:09:03,958 --> 00:09:05,416
What are you
guys talking about?

134
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,125
What is this thing she has?

135
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,666
Something
that is a receptacle

136
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:10,166
for magical knowledge.

137
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,666
It can function on its
own as a magical array.

138
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:15,625
It works independently
of the magician's will.

139
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:17,625
An original grimoire.

140
00:09:17,708 --> 00:09:19,375
[STIYL] You think so...?
Creating a grimoire to fit

141
00:09:19,458 --> 00:09:21,166
these exact circumstances.

142
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:22,666
That would be quite difficult.

143
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:24,166
[TSUCHIMIKADO] The
original text could just be

144
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:27,291
a scribbled note. It would
have limited effectiveness...

145
00:09:27,375 --> 00:09:29,583
and it would break down quickly.

146
00:09:29,666 --> 00:09:31,041
Let's call it "Shorthand."

147
00:09:31,125 --> 00:09:32,708
That should be accurate enough.

148
00:09:32,791 --> 00:09:35,083
Okay, fine. But what does
that mean we should do?

149
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:36,666
First thing...
we have to take out

150
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:38,458
the automatic intercept spell.

151
00:09:38,541 --> 00:09:41,458
For that, we're going to need
to be able to use Stiyl's magic.

152
00:09:41,541 --> 00:09:43,125
And what are the
chances of her fleeing

153
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:45,583
the search area while
we're doing that?

154
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,625
[TSUCHIMIKADO] If she
was so sure that she could

155
00:09:47,708 --> 00:09:49,666
get away cleanly, I
don't think she'd go to

156
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:52,541
the trouble of setting
up an intercept spell, do you?

157
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:53,583
[STIYL] Hmm...

158
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:54,833
Okay, Stiyl...

159
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:57,083
You need to try using
your magic on something.

160
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:02,083
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
A divination circle.

161
00:10:02,166 --> 00:10:04,208
This is a yet-unused
magical array,

162
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:06,375
and it doesn't
employ anyone's magic.

163
00:10:06,458 --> 00:10:07,708
[TSUCHIMIKADO] It will
activate in response to

164
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:09,916
the power of the intercept
spell, providing us with

165
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,625
the direction and distance.

166
00:10:12,708 --> 00:10:13,708
Now then...

167
00:10:13,791 --> 00:10:15,791
[KAMIJO] Hold on,
Tsuchimikado...

168
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:18,666
To make it work, won't he have
to use his magic one more time?

169
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:20,125
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Are you kidding?

170
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:22,000
Who said anything
about one time...?

171
00:10:22,083 --> 00:10:23,750
If we don't find the
Shorthand's location

172
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:24,916
the first time around,

173
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,875
we'll have to keep
trying over and over.

174
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:27,916
[KAMIJO] You bastard!

175
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,250
Easy... You seem to have

176
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:32,125
