00:13:13,958 --> 00:13:15,750
of some magical effort.

246
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:18,833
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Of course,
if my ability to use magic

247
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:20,416
wasn't so handicapped...

248
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,708
Stiyl wouldn't have
to go through this.

249
00:13:22,791 --> 00:13:24,166
That much is true...

250
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:26,208
So you can go
ahead and blame me.

251
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:28,625
Although... I will
not be stopped from

252
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:31,416
finding the Shorthand
and destroying it.

253
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,125
[TSUCHIMIKADO] I also
intend to catch Oriana

254
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:35,208
and personally see to
it that the Stab Sword

255
00:13:35,291 --> 00:13:36,958
deal is off for good...

256
00:13:37,041 --> 00:13:39,625
Now, Kami... Your map.

257
00:13:40,416 --> 00:13:41,583
I want to know
what's three hundred

258
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:43,666
and two meters
northwest of here...

259
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:46,791
Because that's where we can
find the Shorthand grimoire.

260
00:13:46,875 --> 00:13:48,458
Uh... okay...

261
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:54,833
[KAMIJO] Looks like...

262
00:13:54,916 --> 00:13:56,000
[gasps]

263
00:13:56,083 --> 00:13:58,083
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
It's a middle school?!

264
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:03,291
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
Great, a festival!

265
00:14:03,375 --> 00:14:05,041
And the event's
about to start...!

266
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:06,416
All of the spectators
and cameras

267
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,000
are already there by now.

268
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:09,333
Guess sneaking around
isn't going to do us

269
00:14:09,416 --> 00:14:10,750
any good this time.

270
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:12,083
Okay then,
what's the plan...?

271
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:14,000
We're not gonna sit back
and do nothing, right?

272
00:14:14,083 --> 00:14:15,041
I suppose
we'll just have to

273
00:14:15,125 --> 00:14:16,708
pretend to be contestants.

274
00:14:16,791 --> 00:14:18,458
[KAMIJO] Don't you
have a better idea...?

275
00:14:18,541 --> 00:14:19,958
We're in high school, man!

276
00:14:20,041 --> 00:14:22,208
How're we gonna pass
for middle schoolers?

277
00:14:24,583 --> 00:14:26,166
[KAMIJO] Damn!

278
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:27,791
We need to get in
there, and quickly.

279
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:29,583
There's a decent risk
that the intercept spell

280
00:14:29,666 --> 00:14:31,291
might turn on others, too.

281
00:14:31,375 --> 00:14:32,625
[KAMIJO] Huh?

282
00:14:32,708 --> 00:14:33,708
Do you know what the
easiest and most common way

283
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:36,083
of triggering a
magic ritual is, Kami?

284
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:37,833
[TSUCHIMIKADO] By touching.

285
00:14:37,916 --> 00:14:39,833
A regular person with
no knowledge of magic

286
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:42,125
still has a chance of
activating the intercept

287
00:14:42,208 --> 00:14:43,708
spell by touching it.

288
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:44,916
Now, they don't
have the kind of

289
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,250
defenses a magician
has, so if that happens,

290
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,833
they'll be in real danger.

291
00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:51,208
At any rate, let's hurry...

292
00:14:51,291 --> 00:14:52,625
We've gotta get to
that intercept spell

293
00:14:52,708 --> 00:14:54,208
before it hurts anyone.

294
00:14:54,291 --> 00:14:55,416
[KAMIJO] All right!

295
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,666
[TSUCHIMIKADO] And to
help us with that...

296
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:03,583
[lauhging]

297
00:15:03,666 --> 00:15:04,916
Egh!

298
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,041
Cannon ball!

299
00:15:07,125 --> 00:15:08,416
Uuhhh.

300
00:15:10,583 --> 00:15:12,500
[TSUCHIMIKADO] I'm sorry,
sir. Excuse me...

301
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:14,583
Our event is the next one
up, but were kinda' hopin'

302
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:16,041
we wouldn't have to
go into on to the field

303
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:18,000
lookin' like this,
ya know what I mean?

304
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:20,166
[TSUCHIMIKADO] My mom
wants pictures and stuff...

305
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:21,666
Doesn't everyone's?

306
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:24,000
And I suppose that you're hoping
to change your gym clothes.

307
00:15:24,083 --> 00:15:26,083
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Ahhh
Yes, sir...! We are...!

308
00:15:26,166 --> 00:15:28,000
But obviously, they're
in the locker room.

309
00:15:28,083 --> 00:15:31,416
Yeah... you can go in,
just make it quick.

310
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,000
But rules are still rules...

311
00:15:33,083 --> 00:15:35,833
I'll need to check
your IDs before you pass.

312
00:15:37,375 --> 00:15:38,583
You know, I--

313
00:15:38,666 --> 00:15:39,375
[TSUCHIMIKADO chuckles]

314
00:15:39,458 --> 00:15:41,291
Okay...! Here ya go, sir!

315
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:44,291
Ugh...!
Come on, kid...!

316
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:46,541
Would it have killed you
to wipe off your muddy hand?

317
00:15:46,625 --> 00:15:48,750
Oh, well... Go on...
They usually don't

318
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:50,333
let students enter late.

319
00:15:50,416 --> 00:15:52,625
[TSUCHIMIKADO]
Thank you so much, man!

320
00:15:55,041 --> 00:15:56,791
Well...? We're not
exactly gonna blend in

321
00:15:56,875 --> 00:15:58,000
looking like this, you know.

322
00:15:58,083 --> 00:15:59,625
Yep... I'm guessing
there are changes

323
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:02,750
of clothing in the nurse's
office. We'll look there.

324
00:16:04,791 --> 00:16:05,625
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER 9A]
The next event will be

325
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:07,125
the ball toss competition.

326
00:16:07,208 --> 00:16:08,958
This event will see
two hundred students from

327
00:16:09,041 --> 00:16:10,875
Minamizawa Middle
School pitted against

328
00:16:10,958 --> 00:16:13,375
twenty students from
Tokiwadai Middle School.

329
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:24,500
[crowd cheering]

330
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:26,750
[GIRL lauhging]

331
00:16:26,833 --> 00:16:28,666
You can smell fear
radiating from them

332
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:32,291
like a fine perfume...
I like your scent, gentlemen.

333
00:16:32,375 --> 00:16:34,375
[GIRLS giggle]

334
00:16:35,875 --> 00:16:38,833
[MIKOTO] What exactly
is the meaning of this...?

335
00:16:38,916 --> 00:16:40,375
What is he doing?!

336
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:43,666
[MIKOTO] He doesn't even
belong in this event...! Jeez!

337
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:46,541
No...! Tokiwadai?
You're kidding me!

338
00:16:46,625 --> 00:16:48,791
They've got some
serious espers over there!

339
00:16:48,875 --> 00:16:50,583
Oh, do they...?
Well, I guess we should

340
00:16:50,666 --> 00:16:53,291
watch out for stray
shots, then, shouldn't we?

341
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:56,541
If the Shorthand is
here, where would it be?

342
00:16:56,625 --> 00:16:57,875
Where should we look?

343
00:16:57,958 --> 00:17:00,500
I'd say the baskets are
the most likely place.

344
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:02,541
[TSUCHIMIKADO] They probably
borrowed some from elsewhere,

345
00:17:02,625 --> 00:17:03,791
so they could have
been rigged before

346
00:17:03,875 --> 00:17:05,750
they were even brought here.

347
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:09,083
I'm going to go through and
check each basket in order.

348
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:10,333
[TSUCHIMIKADO] As for you,

349
00:17:10,416 --> 00:17:12,458
your work begins once
I find the Shorthand.

350
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:17,500
[crowd cheering]

351
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:21,291
Everybody ready...?
Get set! And, go!

352
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:27,333
[BOYS yelling]

353
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:28,708
What're you
standing there for?

354
00:17:28,791 --> 00:17:30,208
Get moving, Kami!

355
00:17:30,291 --> 00:17:31,625
Oh... Right!

356
00:17:31,708 --> 00:17:41,708
♪

357
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,666
[KAMIJO] Is that the one?

358
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:49,500
[TSUCHIMIKADO] No, this isn't
it... Let's keep on moving.

359
00:17:55,750 --> 00:17:56,958
Huh?

360
00:17:57,041 --> 00:17:59,333
[TSUCHIMIKADO] Not that
one, either... C'mon!

361
00:17:59,416 --> 00:18:00,333
[KAMIJO] Ah!

362
00:18:00,416 --> 00:18:10,375
[BOYS yelling]

363
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:16,958
[KAMIJO] Watch out!

364
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:20,791
Hey, Kami! You can
use my back to jump!

365
00:18:26,416 --> 00:18:27,791
[KAMIJO] Quick,
you need to move!

366
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:38,583
[STUDENTS gasping]

367
00:18:38,666 --> 00:18:40,083
[rumble]

368
00:18:40,166 --> 00:18:44,416
[crowd cheering]

369
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:48,250
[breathing heavy]

370
00:18:48,333 --> 00:18:50,500
You know, I really
can't believe this!

371
00:18:50,583 --> 00:18:53,166
[MIKOTO] That you
would take it this far!

372
00:18:53,250 --> 00:18:54,916
Just so I would lose
our bet and have to play

373
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,875
your dumb penalty game!

374
00:18:57,583 --> 00:18:58,958
[GIRL screams]

375
00:19:04,750 --> 00:19:07,750
[MIKOTO] Honestly! I had
to do something, you jerk,

376
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:10,000
or you were gonna
get yourself hurt.

377
00:19:11,291 --> 00:19:12,958
[KAMIJO] Misaka!

378
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:15,083
Don't touch that!

379
00:19:15,166 --> 00:19:17,708
Huh...? What's wrong?

380
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:19,041
[KAMIJO] Listen to me, okay...?

381
00:19:19,125 --> 00:19:21,125
I'll explain
everything, I promise.

382
00:19:21,208 --> 00:19:23,083
Just move away from there!

383
00:19:23,166 --> 00:19:24,916
What...? Move away? Why?

384
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,250
What are you talking about...?

385
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:27,541
I still don't know
what you're doing

386
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:29,375
competing in a
middle school event...

387
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:31,708
How about you explain
yourself and then--

388
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:37,541
[KAMIJO] You stay
out of this, kid!

389
00:19:39,458 --> 00:19:42,625
[KAMIJO] Don't argue!
Just come over here, please.

390
00:19:42,708 --> 00:19:43,708
Uh?

391
00:19:43,791 --> 00:19:45,833
You're in danger
standing there!

392
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:50,250
[MIKOTO] What...? You're
being stupid! Please...!

393
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:51,291
You don't really
think I needed you

394
00:19:51,375 --> 00:19:53,083
to defend me from that guy?

395
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:54,916
I can take care of myself!

396
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,291
Now, how about that
explanation you offered?

397
00:19:57,375 --> 00:19:59,125
Like I said,
I'll tell you later!

398
00:19:59,208 --> 00:20:00,750
[KAMIJO]
That spot is dangerous.

399
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:03,583
I don't want you getting
hurt. It's that simple!

400
00:20:06,916 --> 00:20:10,416
[MIKOTO] Me? Get hurt? I don't
need you protecting me...

401
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:13,166
I don't care how sweet
you're being. I'm fine...

402
00:20:15,916 --> 00:20:18,625
That's it! You startled
me and now I'm babbling.

403
00:20:18,708 --> 00:20:20,708
Just leave me alone
already, will you?

404
00:20:21,791 --> 00:20:23,375
Uh--What the--?

405
00:20:31,375 --> 00:20:32,625
[KAMIJO] Just keep quiet...

406
00:20:32,708 --> 00:20:34,666
Hold still for a second.

407
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:38,416
[MIKOTO] Um... I, uh...

408
00:20:39,791 --> 00:20:42,541
I'm too late...! C'mon!
Talk to me, Misaka.

409
00:20:42,625 --> 00:20:44,708
Do you have a fever?
Does it hurt?

410
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:45,916
Ugh!

411
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,500
What do you
mean?! I'm fine!

412
00:20:47,583 --> 00:20:50,666
Hey, Tsuchimikado...!
It's over here on this pole!

413
00:20:52,458 --> 00:20:54,291
[KAMIJO] I was wrong!

414
00:20:54,375 --> 00:20:56,541
[wistle blows]

415
00:20:56,625 --> 00:20:58,958
You again, Kamijo...?
This is ridiculous!

416
00:20:59,041 --> 00:21:00,500
Why are you even here?

417
00:21:00,583 --> 00:21:02,541
I was wondering why you ran
off in such a hurry before,

418
00:21:02,625 --> 00:21:05,166
but I didn't expect
this! Explain yourself!

419
00:21:05,250 --> 00:21:07,458
Now we'll have to
restart the whole event!

420
00:21:08,041 --> 00:21:09,416
[screams]

421
00:21:15,333 --> 00:21:16,708
Fukiyose!

422
00:21:16,791 --> 00:21:18,875
Whoa... What happened?

423
00:21:21,916 --> 00:21:23,916
Hurry up. You need
to go and touch her.

424
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,583
She's got no magical
defense. She won't last...

425
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:27,958
Get over there, now!

426
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:38,875
Please, Fukiyose...!
You have to wake up!

427
00:21:38,958 --> 00:21:40,583
[KAMIJO] Just open your eyes!

428
00:21:40,666 --> 00:21:50,666
♪

429
00:22:01,083 --> 00:22:02,250
Fine, Oriana Thomson...

430
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:03,958
I've had enough of this.

431
00:22:06,458 --> 00:22:08,000
You're not gonna
be dictating the terms

432
00:22:08,083 --> 00:22:09,708
of this fight anymore.

433
00:22:09,791 --> 00:22:11,166
You lost that
privilege when you

434
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:13,166
started involving
innocent people...

435
00:22:13,250 --> 00:22:14,583
If you think I'm
going to stand around

436
00:22:14,666 --> 00:22:16,416
and let you keep
hurting them, then...

437
00:22:18,458 --> 00:22:20,875
[KAMIJO] I'll show you
just how wrong you are.

438
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:22,916
I hope you're ready...

439
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,833
'cause I won't be showing
any mercy when I come for you.

440
00:22:25,916 --> 00:22:35,875
♪ [Ending Song] ♪

441
00:23:56,458 --> 00:23:57,833
[KAMIJO]
Fukiyose has collapsed...

442
00:23:57,916 --> 00:24:00,458
Stiyl and Tsuchimikado are
in the line of fire, too.

443
00:24:00,541 --> 00:24:03,125
If the Stab Sword is the
reason for all this...

444
00:24:03,208 --> 00:24:05,375
I swear I'm gonna destroy it.

445
00:24:05,458 --> 00:24:06,833
Next time, "Shorthand."

446
00:24:06,916 --> 00:24:09,833
When science and magic
cross paths, a story is born.

